article.description: — Cobe Williams had a career-high 20 points as Louisiana Tech got past Louisiana-Lafayette 78-69 on Saturday.
article.headline: Williams with 20, Louisiana Tech beats Louisiana-Lafayette
article.linkText: Williams with 20, Louisiana Tech beats Louisiana-Lafayette
article.story: RUSTON, La. -- — Cobe Williams had a career-high 20 points as Louisiana Tech got past Louisiana-Lafayette 78-69 on Saturday. Amorie Archibald had 18 points for Louisiana Tech (7-2), which earned its fifth consecutive home victory. Kenneth Lofton Jr. added 17 points and 10 rebounds. Jordan Brown scored a career-high 30 points for the Ragin' Cajuns (5-4), making 13 of 18 field goals. Joe Charles added 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
